gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Bucks 141, Pistons 135
gameRecap.excerpt: The Bucks defeated the Pistons, 141-135. Damian Lillard led the way for the Bucks with a season-high 45 points (5-11 3pt. FG), along with six rebounds and 11 assists, while Giannis Antetokounmpo added 31 points, 10 rebounds and nine assists in the victory. Ausar Thompson tallied a career-high 22 points (10-15 FG) for the Pistons in the losing effort. The Bucks improve to 29-13 on the season, while the Pistons fall to 4-38.
